The May 31 broadcast featured interviews with former Florida Gov. Jeb Bush and CIA Director John Brennan. Nearly 4 million viewers tuned in to see Bob Schieffers last show, he was the of Face the Nation for 24 years.
In addition to winning eight Emmys, Schieffer was named a living legend by the Library of Congress in 2008 and inducted into the Television Academy Hall of Fame in 2013.
